Hello, how can I help you?

29
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:11,310
I wanted to get a new card since it's old.

30
00:04:11,310 --> 00:04:15,200
How would you like the new debit card, then?

31
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:18,600
It's easy to get cash back.
Many people get it to save easily.

32
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,980
I'll go with that, then.

33
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:22,510
Okay. Please wait until the card gets made.

34
00:04:22,510 --> 00:04:24,110
Okay.

35
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:33,380
You have a plan for small businesses, too.

36
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:36,130
Yes, we do. We have many plans.

37
00:04:36,130 --> 00:04:40,300
We provide low-interest loans
and investment classes.

38
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:42,750
Okay, here's the card.

39
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:46,170
I'll give you the stickers to decorate the card.

40
00:04:46,170 --> 00:04:49,280
How cute. Thank you.

41
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:01,410
Attorney Kang, Seoul Central District Court

42
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:05,220
is asking if you can be the public
defender for a trial on May 10.

43
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:06,400
What should I tell them?

44
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:09,200
- Tell them I'm available.
- Okay.

45
00:05:16,980 --> 00:05:18,490
This is your first case as a public defender.

46
00:05:18,490 --> 00:05:21,340
Yes. I finally get to have one.

47
00:05:21,340 --> 00:05:22,520
What kind of case is it?

48
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:24,120
I'm not sure yet.

49
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:27,780
They just asked if I was available.

50
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:30,280
Did you get approval from Ms. Kang?

51
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:33,400
I signed up because she approved a while ago.

52
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,100
Things got a bit awkward during
the inheritance renouncing case.

53
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,680
Maybe I should ask her again.

54
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:42,290
Didn't a strange old man visit
your office this morning?

55
00:05:42,290 --> 00:05:44,150
Huh? Did he go there, too?

56
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:46,980
He brought a strange paper with Chinese characters

57
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:48,880
and said he owns a huge plot of land.

58
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:52,860
Yes. He brought a document that
belongs in the National Archives.

59
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:54,650
You've never even been there.

60
00:05:54,650 --> 00:05:56,770
- Have you, then?
- Of course, I have.

61
00:05:56,770 --> 00:05:59,090
I had a decorated veteran case once.

62
00:05:59,090 --> 00:06:01,900
According to what our partner said,

63
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:04,120
he's been to many firms.

64
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:07,400
Because he said he can't pay the legal fee.

65
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,200
- We must've kicked him out, then.
- Probably.

66
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:13,390
I thought your partner would accept the case.

67
00:06:13,390 --> 00:06:16,740
My partner isn't that easy, either.

68
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:18,820
I see.

69
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:26,320
What's the deal? The lunch hour
isn't even over yet.

70
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:28,800
- What is it?
- Our partner is looking for me. I have to go.

71
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,540
I'll clean up. You can go.

72
00:06:30,540 --> 00:06:31,940
Thanks. Let's go.

73
00:06:31,940 --> 00:06:33,460
Okay.

74
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,800
Let's go to the cafe. I need caffeine.

75
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:40,100
No, no. I have a lot to do, too.

76
00:06:42,210 --> 00:06:44,880
I can't go to the cafe, either.

77
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,200
- Would you like one?
- Sure.

78
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:51,620
- Would you like one, too?
- Thank you.

79
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:53,060
Here you go.

80
00:06:53,690 --> 00:06:55,660
I feel better now.

81
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:59,610
- Gosh.
- Let's go.

82
00:07:01,940 --> 00:07:03,650
Sunbae, clean up first!

83
00:07:03,650 --> 00:07:06,960
I want you two to take a real estate case.

84
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,990
Are we taking that old man's case?

85
00:07:08,990 --> 00:07:09,990
You know about it?

86
00:07:09,990 --> 00:07:13,630
Yes, I heard from other attorneys.

87
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,850
It's unusual for you to take a case like this.

88
00:07:16,850 --> 00:07:18,180
What's "A case like this"?

89
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:20,690
I heard he can't pay the legal fee.

90
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:25,030
We'll get a share if he gets the land back.

91
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:26,510
It's a pretty sizable land.

92
00:07:26,510 --> 00:07:30,470
We agreed to pay the trial expenses,

93
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:33,570
but we'd score big if we win.

94
00:07:33,570 --> 00:07:35,630
Please take it.

95
00:07:40,180 --> 00:07:43,090
- Is this all?
- Yes, that's apparently all of it.

96
00:07:43,090 --> 00:07:46,130
W-What do we do with just this?

97
00:07:46,130 --> 00:07:48,980
Will you really do stuff like this?

98
00:07:52,710 --> 00:07:54,950
What's with everyone these days?

99
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:57,820
You have a lot of complaints.

100
00:07:57,820 --> 00:08:01,170
Let's just do as we normally do.

101
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,070
Okay?

102
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:16,470
Yes, Attorney Kang. How can I help you?

103
00:08:17,690 --> 00:08:19,390
Ms. Kang,

104
00:08:20,380 --> 00:08:24,530
I got a call for a public defense case.

105
00:08:24,530 --> 00:08:26,120
Could I take it?

106
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:29,740
Of course. You didn't have to ask me that.

107
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,570
I wanted to make sure.

108
00:08:33,550 --> 00:08:36,640
I said you could last time.

109
00:08:38,740 --> 00:08:41,380
Yes. Thank you.

110
00:08:42,370 --> 00:08:45,950
Create a system where you can share a new case

111
00:08:45,950 --> 00:08:49,090
info immediately for each floor, please.

112
00:08:49,090 --> 00:08:52,340
So, we won't be taking the same
case on the opposing side.

113
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:54,200
And...

114
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:58,890
allow each floor to hire their own
accountant and create records, too.

115
00:08:58,890 --> 00:09:01,680
Will you continue to work here, Executive Director?

116
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:05,010
Must be hard going back and forth
between here and the foundation.

117
00:09:05,010 --> 00:09:08,250
- I'm sorry.
- No, I'm okay.

118
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:11,840
But people are saying you
only care about the law firm.

119
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:15,760
Both the foundation and the
company employees say that.

120
00:09:16,580 --> 00:09:20,530
The employees and executives are doing great.

121
00:09:20,530 --> 00:09:22,840
I was feeling thankful.

122
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:25,600
I guess I've been kind of lax.

123
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:28,800
Thank you for letting me know.
I'll be more careful.

124
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:34,110
This law firm isn't your foundation work or your business.

125
00:09:34,110 --> 00:09:38,810
May I ask why you care about it so much?

126
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:20,000
Yes. Looks good.

127
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,910
I'll take these two.

128
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:24,060
- Please take the rest.
- Okay.

129
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:25,950
Right, we got another case.

130
00:10:25,950 --> 00:10:28,330
It's a real estate contract issue.

131
00:10:28,330 --> 00:10:30,730
The client is young. Please have
a consultation with him.

132
00:10:30,730 --> 00:10:32,270
Got it.

133
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:34,500
Have you...

134
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,590
thought about what I gave you?

135
00:10:36,590 --> 00:10:39,620
The doctoral program.

136
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,900
Yes. That.

137
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:44,580
Thank you for thinking of me,

138
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:47,820
but I'm not going to do it.

139
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:49,260
Why not?

140
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:53,110
They don't hire you after if you work
while in the program.

141
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:54,420
Did the school say that?

142
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:56,170
Yes.

143
00:10:56,170 --> 00:10:58,340
I should be working here.

144
00:10:58,340 --> 00:11:00,380
I'm not going anywhere and leaving you behind.

145
00:11:00,380 --> 00:11:04,430
I'll go to my office to work, then.

146
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:07,930
Okay...

147
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:13,510
Attorneys aren't supposed
to be sitting around all the time.

148
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:15,650
You need to be on your feet.

149
00:12:15,650 --> 00:12:19,350
Or be better at listening.

150
00:12:20,660 --> 00:12:23,890
So, after the liberation and the Korean War,

151
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:26,490
other people took this land from you.

152
00:12:26,490 --> 00:12:28,050
That's right.

153
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:30,380
After the war ended,

154
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:35,200
the ownership suddenly went to the Kwak family.

155
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:38,730
We can't confirm much
with just this piece of paper.

156
00:12:38,730 --> 00:12:42,230
Do things change if there are two pieces of paper?

157
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:44,870
There was only one to begin with.

158
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:48,280
The attorneys should be figuring out the rest.

159
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:50,700
Here, here, here. Look, look.

160
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:52,930
Here.

161
00:12:52,930 --> 00:12:54,760
Doheung-myeon.

162
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:56,750
It's Doheung-eup now.

163
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:59,030
No. 580.

164
00:12:59,030 --> 00:13:06,590
Here. 39,554 pyeong.

165
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:08,630
Daejeong Year Three.

166
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:12,240
Daejeong is a period when
we were occupied by Japan.

167
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:14,450
And here. Han In Su.

168
00:13:14,450 --> 00:13:16,900
I understand what's written there.

169
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:20,800
We're saying we can't tell what
happened from this alone.

170
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:24,620
The address that's written here
doesn't exist anymore.

171
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:28,300
What's your relationship
to Mr. Han In Su, Mr. Park?

172
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:32,390
- We're family.
- What's your relationship specifically?

173
00:13:32,390 --> 00:13:35,670
It means we're closer than any family.

174
00:13:35,670 --> 00:13:38,080
You aren't family just because you share blood.

175
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:39,930
You mean you aren't related, right?

176
00:13:39,930 --> 00:13:42,280
Come on. Look, look.

177
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:46,430
I'm not trying to take back my land.

178
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:47,720
Look at this.

179
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:51,200
They're Han In Su's great-grandchildren.

180
00:13:52,010 --> 00:13:54,420
So, you aren't related to him at all.

181
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:57,270
Why are you trying to get this land back?

182
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:04,680
Everyone in the neighborhood knows
the land belongs to Mr. Han.

183
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:07,310
But no one's saying anything.

184
00:14:07,310 --> 00:14:12,630
Why? Because all the elders
in his family had passed away.

185
00:14:14,090 --> 00:14:16,500
Come with me. You'll see when you go there.

186
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:19,870
- We don't need to go.
- Let's go.

187
00:14:19,870 --> 00:14:22,250
What? Really? Really? Really?

188
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:24,680
Okay, let's get going.

189
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:26,560
Let's get going now.

190
00:14:29,420 --> 00:14:31,500
Are you really going?

191
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:34,900
We need to check if the power
of attorney is real. Let's go.

192
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:49,060
I signed a contract through a real estate agency,

193
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:53,100
but the owner told me to leave,
saying they never signed that contract.

194
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,840
You've never met the owners?

195
00:14:54,840 --> 00:15:00,000
No. The real estate agency said
they had the power of attorney.

196
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:03,120
They even showed me the document.

197
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:06,530
Power of attorney...

198
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:09,340
The power of attorney document isn't here.

199
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:14,590
They said I can only see it,
but they can't give it to me.

200
00:15:14,590 --> 00:15:17,440
That's not true. If you haven't met the owner,

201
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:20,730
you have to make sure you
have the power of attorney.

202
00:15:21,470 --> 00:15:23,450
If so,

203
00:15:23,450 --> 00:15:26,680
I messed that up, too.

204
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:29,040
Did you sign alone?

205
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:33,010
I used to live in an orphanage.

206
00:15:33,010 --> 00:15:36,190
I barely managed to get this
with the independence fund.

207
00:15:36,190 --> 00:15:39,100
I had no one to ask about it.

208
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:40,740
I see.

209
00:15:42,470 --> 00:15:44,340
It's okay. This isn't your fault, Yun Su.

210
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:47,270
These people are the bad ones.

211
00:15:48,260 --> 00:15:52,340
I think the agency created a fake contract

212
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:54,130
to take your security deposit.

213
00:15:54,130 --> 00:15:57,230
I was settling down there,

214
00:15:57,230 --> 00:16:00,500
but they suddenly sent an eviction notice.

215
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,580
I don't know what's going on.

216
00:16:02,580 --> 00:16:06,250
I have nowhere to go if I get kicked out.

217
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:08,270
It's okay. Yun Su,

218
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:11,170
you know where the agency is located, right?

219
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:16,570
It wasn't me.

220
00:16:16,570 --> 00:16:19,490
It was an employee I had.

221
00:16:19,490 --> 00:16:22,710
I don't know where he went now.

222
00:16:22,710 --> 00:16:26,340
Tell him, young man. I didn't do it.

223
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:34,180
Even so, if your employee did,

224
00:16:34,180 --> 00:16:37,560
you still have the employer's liability.

225
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,940
I'll compensate if I have to.

226
00:16:39,940 --> 00:16:42,070
Go ahead and sue.

227
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:46,200
Did you work with the landlord for a long time?

228
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:48,230
He owns the entire studio apartment building.

229
00:16:48,230 --> 00:16:50,060
Yes. I've worked with him for a long time.

230
00:16:50,060 --> 00:16:53,530
But not anymore because of this.

231
00:16:53,530 --> 00:16:56,610
Is he an understanding person, then?

232
00:16:56,610 --> 00:17:00,590
Gosh, no. He's strictly by the book.

233
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:07,880
Your employee showed a power
of attorney to Yun Su.

234
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:10,290
What's that about?

235
00:17:11,730 --> 00:17:14,600
There couldn't have been a power of attorney.

236
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:33,290
Why did this happen only to me?

237
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:35,780
Don't think about it like that.

238
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,760
It's my fault for not looking into it.

239
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:41,150
I know. But...

240
00:17:41,150 --> 00:17:45,470
everyone in that building signed
the contract through them.

241
00:17:45,470 --> 00:17:48,630
People live there without any issues.

242
00:17:48,630 --> 00:17:51,390
Why did this only happen to me?

243
00:17:58,530 --> 00:18:02,620
You just had a bit of bad luck.
There's no other reason.

244
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:45,740
Everyone signed the contract through that agency.

245
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:49,240
But no one else had any issues.

246
00:19:14,910 --> 00:19:16,090
(speech)

247
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:18,000
This place was designated

248
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:21,760
as an industrial complex zone or something.

249
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:24,890
The property values skyrocketed.

250
00:19:24,890 --> 00:19:28,530
I tried to forget about it, but hearing that

251
00:19:28,530 --> 00:19:32,530
made me so angry. I couldn't just sit still.

252
00:19:32,530 --> 00:19:34,250
All of this belonged to one person?

253
00:19:34,250 --> 00:19:35,630
Yes.

254
00:19:35,630 --> 00:19:39,300
The Kwak family shared it among themselves.

255
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:42,330
The government took some, too.

256
00:19:42,330 --> 00:19:45,120
- What about beyond this stream?
- Huh?

257
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:47,430
No, no. Not there.

258
00:19:47,430 --> 00:19:49,350
Make it quick.

259
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:51,150
I'm already 80 and...

260
00:19:51,150 --> 00:19:56,000
Mr. Han's great-grandchildren
aren't young, either.

261
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,480
Why aren't they doing anything?

262
00:19:59,430 --> 00:20:02,600
Because all of the elders
