00:40:32,410 --> 00:40:36,430
Please check if there are
scholarship certifications left.

532
00:40:36,430 --> 00:40:38,230
Yes.

533
00:40:38,230 --> 00:40:41,750
No, you should have them, Mom.

534
00:40:41,750 --> 00:40:45,310
It's because there's someone I want to help.

535
00:40:45,310 --> 00:40:48,970
Okay, okay. Got it. Bye.

536
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:12,070
Have you thought about it?

537
00:41:12,070 --> 00:41:14,110
- About what?
- Joining the company.

538
00:41:14,110 --> 00:41:16,190
I'm not doing it. It doesn't suit me.

539
00:41:16,190 --> 00:41:17,610
You think being an attorney suits you?

540
00:41:17,610 --> 00:41:20,380
I won't run a business even
if I quit being an attorney.

541
00:41:20,380 --> 00:41:23,540
I would've joined your company
from the beginning if I were interested.

542
00:41:23,540 --> 00:41:27,200
I didn't start the business
because I loved it, either.

543
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:30,010
I eventually found what suits me.
That's what happened.

544
00:41:30,010 --> 00:41:33,020
I didn't become an attorney
because I loved it, either.

545
00:41:33,020 --> 00:41:35,790
But I'll try to find what suits me.

546
00:41:35,790 --> 00:41:37,070
Seriously.

547
00:41:37,070 --> 00:41:39,460
You got your stubbornness from me.

548
00:41:39,460 --> 00:41:40,700
I know.

549
00:41:40,700 --> 00:41:43,660
That's why running the business
would suit you, too.

550
00:41:43,660 --> 00:41:45,460
Seriously.

551
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:48,000
I have a plan, too.

552
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:50,220
- What plan?
- Just wait and see.

553
00:41:50,220 --> 00:41:52,800
I'm preparing something.

554
00:42:08,210 --> 00:42:09,860
What about beyond this stream?

555
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:12,570
No, no. Not there.

556
00:42:17,560 --> 00:42:20,140
That old man was talking nonsense, then.

557
00:42:20,140 --> 00:42:22,800
He was either mistaken or lying.

558
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:26,900
Nothing works in this neighborhood without him.

559
00:42:26,900 --> 00:42:29,000
Hey.

560
00:42:30,680 --> 00:42:34,030
Do you feel for that old man, your client?

561
00:42:34,030 --> 00:42:37,810
I wanted what Mr. Park said to be true.

562
00:42:37,810 --> 00:42:39,840
Including how he was doing it out of goodwill.

563
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:44,240
Do you only do what benefits you?

564
00:42:44,240 --> 00:42:46,880
Who else would do this but me?

565
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:51,210
I'm doing it because someone needs to.

566
00:42:58,340 --> 00:43:01,760
He brought a document that
belongs in the National Archives.

567
00:43:01,760 --> 00:43:03,610
You've never even been there.

568
00:43:03,610 --> 00:43:05,430
- Have you, then?
- Of course, I have.

569
00:43:05,430 --> 00:43:09,770
I had a decorated veteran case once.

570
00:43:21,650 --> 00:43:24,128
The National Archives documents
are public now, right?

571
00:43:24,128 --> 00:43:25,240
Huh?

572
00:43:26,270 --> 00:43:29,510
No. 580, Dongjan-ri.

573
00:43:30,230 --> 00:43:32,770
Here. Check the one that says "Han In Su."

574
00:43:32,770 --> 00:43:34,320
Okay.

575
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:39,800
Let's print everything under Han In Su.

576
00:43:39,800 --> 00:43:42,340
Okay.

577
00:43:43,070 --> 00:43:46,840
No. 580 was one big lot back then.

578
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:50,310
But the shape is different than
what the old man said.

579
00:44:08,630 --> 00:44:10,160
This part?

580
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:11,890
(speech) Here.

581
00:44:21,380 --> 00:44:24,390
I'll print the registers for these areas.

582
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:39,390
384...

583
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:57,600
130,757.1

584
00:44:57,600 --> 00:45:04,080
In pyeong, it's 39,554.

585
00:45:04,080 --> 00:45:10,260
Here. 39,554 pyeong.

586
00:45:10,260 --> 00:45:12,920
Mr. Park Man Su was right.

587
00:45:53,670 --> 00:45:55,300
Hello.

588
00:45:55,300 --> 00:45:59,110
I'm Attorney Kang Hui Ji, your public defender.

589
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:03,720
Yes.

590
00:46:08,140 --> 00:46:11,580
Isn't it difficult being in the detention center?

591
00:46:13,510 --> 00:46:16,520
I don't need an attorney.

592
00:46:17,230 --> 00:46:20,270
I didn't request a public defender.

593
00:46:20,270 --> 00:46:22,410
Who told you to come here?

594
00:46:22,410 --> 00:46:26,760
The court requires you to have a public defender.

595
00:46:26,760 --> 00:46:28,060
Even if you didn't request it,

596
00:46:28,060 --> 00:46:32,580
you qualify for the court to assign
a public defender for you.

597
00:46:34,390 --> 00:46:39,680
Just do what you need to do and leave.

598
00:46:39,680 --> 00:46:41,910
Don't worry about me.

599
00:46:41,910 --> 00:46:46,860
What I need to do is... to hear your story first.

600
00:46:46,860 --> 00:46:49,870
About what happened and why you did that.

601
00:46:49,870 --> 00:46:53,710
Hearing won't change anything.

602
00:46:53,710 --> 00:46:57,880
I killed Myeong Jae...

603
00:46:59,710 --> 00:47:01,350
and I need to be punished.

604
00:47:01,350 --> 00:47:04,110
Then, your reasons won't be acknowledged.

605
00:47:04,110 --> 00:47:10,310
There are no reasons... to kill someone.

606
00:47:12,200 --> 00:47:17,600
I'm not interested in being
understood or being forgiven, either.

607
00:47:19,850 --> 00:47:21,220
Just leave.

608
00:47:21,220 --> 00:47:24,780
I'm not saying I'll understand you.

609
00:47:24,780 --> 00:47:27,640
I have no right to forgive you, either.

610
00:47:27,640 --> 00:47:31,770
As you said, you'll be punished
regardless of the situation.

611
00:47:33,800 --> 00:47:35,580
Yes.

612
00:47:35,580 --> 00:47:37,780
That's why...

613
00:47:37,780 --> 00:47:40,790
you should let me be punished.

614
00:47:43,850 --> 00:47:46,950
Can I leave...

615
00:47:46,950 --> 00:47:49,300
if you've got nothing more to say?

616
00:48:21,600 --> 00:48:24,750
I killed my younger brother.

617
00:48:24,750 --> 00:48:27,110
I killed him...

618
00:48:27,110 --> 00:48:29,860
and I'll be punished for it.

619
00:48:48,060 --> 00:48:49,650
Yes.

620
00:48:50,900 --> 00:48:55,640
Attorney, Ms. Jeong Sun Ja's children are here.

621
00:48:55,640 --> 00:48:57,700
Her children?

622
00:49:00,210 --> 00:49:04,080
Are you Ms. Jeong's son and daughter?

623
00:49:04,080 --> 00:49:05,610
Yes.

624
00:49:06,310 --> 00:49:08,030
What would happen to Mom?

625
00:49:08,030 --> 00:49:10,490
She'll be on trial soon.

626
00:49:10,490 --> 00:49:12,830
But she won't say anything to me.

627
00:49:12,830 --> 00:49:16,240
It's a bit hard for me to prepare for the trial.

628
00:49:16,240 --> 00:49:20,070
How did she end up living with her brother?

629
00:49:20,070 --> 00:49:23,160
I thought she didn't have children.

630
00:49:27,240 --> 00:49:29,190
The thing is...

631
00:49:29,190 --> 00:49:31,560
Mom was the only family Uncle had.

632
00:49:31,560 --> 00:49:34,790
That's why she lived with him and cared for him.

633
00:49:36,100 --> 00:49:39,950
Did you stay with them sometimes, then?

634
00:49:40,760 --> 00:49:42,200
No.

635
00:49:42,820 --> 00:49:45,370
We didn't think it was something
for us to worry about.

636
00:49:45,370 --> 00:49:49,040
How did Ms. Jeong afford her
living expenses, then?

637
00:49:49,040 --> 00:49:54,910
She probably had a pension
and a caretaking subsidy.

638
00:49:54,910 --> 00:49:57,070
And you didn't help her at all?

639
00:49:57,070 --> 00:50:01,930
No. We couldn't really afford to do so, either.

640
00:50:02,790 --> 00:50:05,080
Can she get out?

641
00:50:10,030 --> 00:50:12,420
The charge is murder.

642
00:50:12,420 --> 00:50:15,270
She can't be released so easily.

643
00:50:16,060 --> 00:50:18,030
Seriously, Uncle...

644
00:50:19,700 --> 00:50:21,830
By chance,

645
00:50:21,830 --> 00:50:24,700
could I visit that house?

646
00:50:24,700 --> 00:50:26,340
Hello?

647
00:50:26,340 --> 00:50:27,900
Why did you call?

648
00:50:27,900 --> 00:50:29,690
I wanted to tell you something.

649
00:50:29,690 --> 00:50:31,590
I'd like you to come to the office sometime.

650
00:50:31,590 --> 00:50:34,210
Why tell me to come if you won't take the case?

651
00:50:34,210 --> 00:50:37,770
I'm not going. I'm busy looking for another firm.

652
00:50:37,770 --> 00:50:39,230
We never said we won't.

653
00:50:39,230 --> 00:50:41,910
We just said there wasn't enough evidence.

654
00:50:41,910 --> 00:50:45,390
Come out. It'd be worth hearing about.

655
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:49,600
How about around five later?

656
00:50:49,600 --> 00:50:52,050
I'll see if I have time.

657
00:50:52,050 --> 00:50:54,110
I'll see you later.

658
00:51:09,520 --> 00:51:11,270
You can go in.

659
00:51:11,270 --> 00:51:13,130
Aren't you coming in with me?

660
00:51:13,130 --> 00:51:17,060
Well, we don't really want to.

661
00:51:17,860 --> 00:51:19,870
Let me know when you're done.

662
00:52:18,640 --> 00:52:22,700
December 31, Tuesday.

663
00:52:22,700 --> 00:52:25,160
He's not responding at all.

664
00:52:25,160 --> 00:52:27,350
My heart filled with tears.

665
00:52:27,350 --> 00:52:29,310
He breathes harshly and rapidly.

666
00:52:29,310 --> 00:52:32,650
December 27. His eyes are open
but not focused.

667
00:52:32,650 --> 00:52:34,310
He doesn't respond to my voice.

668
00:52:34,310 --> 00:52:38,170
I wish I lived just a day longer than Myeong Jae.

669
00:52:38,170 --> 00:52:39,740
December 25.

670
00:52:39,740 --> 00:52:41,460
When I called his name this morning,

671
00:52:41,460 --> 00:52:44,100
he blinked and turned his head slightly.

672
00:52:44,100 --> 00:52:47,360
His eyes looked clear for a brief moment.

673
00:52:47,360 --> 00:52:52,260
He ate a bit of porridge and slept
for a long time as if he were tired.

674
00:52:52,260 --> 00:52:53,920
December 28.

675
00:52:53,920 --> 00:52:57,090
He flinched slightly when I held his hand.

676
00:52:57,090 --> 00:52:59,850
I felt relieved because he looked peaceful.

677
00:52:59,850 --> 00:53:03,150
December 30. I held his hand,
but he had no strength.

678
00:53:03,150 --> 00:53:04,320
He's just receiving fluids.

679
00:53:04,320 --> 00:53:08,030
What do I expect from keeping him alive?

680
00:53:08,030 --> 00:53:13,120
Does he really want to live like this?

681
00:53:13,590 --> 00:53:17,920
December 29. No response at all.

682
00:53:17,920 --> 00:53:20,910
Almost impossible for him to swallow.

683
00:53:22,400 --> 00:53:25,750
No one would listen to me.

684
00:53:26,550 --> 00:53:29,870
No one is interested.

685
00:53:44,390 --> 00:53:47,840
Oh, Ms. Jeong Sun Ja?

686
00:53:47,840 --> 00:53:50,290
Since she didn't quite meet the requirement,

687
00:53:50,290 --> 00:53:53,520
we could only provide minimal support.

688
00:53:53,520 --> 00:53:58,640
It was hard to provide other care
since she has children.

689
00:53:58,640 --> 00:54:01,290
But they apparently neglected her.

690
00:54:01,290 --> 00:54:04,680
You could've provided care if you knew that.

691
00:54:04,680 --> 00:54:07,340
We have our criteria, too.

692
00:54:07,340 --> 00:54:10,940
We wish we could help everyone.

693
00:54:10,940 --> 00:54:12,720
How has she been living, then?

694
00:54:12,720 --> 00:54:15,650
I heard she got an insurance payout,

695
00:54:15,650 --> 00:54:19,430
so she she lived off it and paid
Mr. Jeong's hospital fees, too.

696
00:54:20,460 --> 00:54:21,720
Insurance payout?

697
00:54:21,720 --> 00:54:24,670
Yes. She apparently signed up
for cancer insurance.

698
00:54:24,670 --> 00:54:29,050
But she couldn't spend the money on her treatment.

699
00:54:29,050 --> 00:54:31,490
I hear she's in a late stage.

700
00:54:40,110 --> 00:54:41,930
Thank you.

701
00:54:44,700 --> 00:54:47,210
You look really happy.

702
00:54:47,210 --> 00:54:49,390
So do you.

703
00:54:49,390 --> 00:54:54,260
Mr. Park should be the happy
one since he was right.

704
00:54:54,260 --> 00:54:57,560
Is he not coming because he's upset?

705
00:54:57,560 --> 00:55:00,020
You should've told him that we found a way.

706
00:55:00,020 --> 00:55:03,940
Well, I wanted to tell him in person.

707
00:55:15,120 --> 00:55:18,410
Will you not talk to me today, either?

708
00:55:27,360 --> 00:55:30,340
I'll talk to you, then.

709
00:55:30,340 --> 00:55:36,930
You had no choice but to care
for Mr. Jeong, who had no family.

710
00:55:37,970 --> 00:55:44,230
You didn't want your children
to feel burdened by their uncle.

711
00:55:44,230 --> 00:55:47,000
That's why you couldn't ask them for help.

712
00:55:48,000 --> 00:55:50,690
Instead, you asked the government for help,

713
00:55:50,690 --> 00:55:54,770
but since you didn't quite meet the requirements,

714
00:55:54,770 --> 00:55:58,290
you could only get minimal support.

715
00:55:59,290 --> 00:56:01,620
Ten years have passed like that,

716
00:56:01,620 --> 00:56:04,290
and you started feeling afraid.

717
00:56:05,140 --> 00:56:10,030
"What would happen to Myeong Jae
if I died before him?"

718
00:56:12,120 --> 00:56:15,840
And you learned that you had cancer.

719
00:56:20,020 --> 00:56:22,110
How did you...

720
00:56:24,020 --> 00:56:26,650
find out all that?

721
00:56:29,140 --> 00:56:32,670
I want to hear your story.

722
00:56:37,940 --> 00:56:40,020
No one...

723
00:56:42,420 --> 00:56:46,690
Not a single person listened to me.

724
00:56:47,840 --> 00:56:52,980
The only solution was for me to endure.

725
00:56:52,980 --> 00:56:56,160
I couldn't die before him.

726
00:56:57,030 --> 00:56:58,870
When I...

727
00:57:00,100 --> 00:57:03,950
learned that I had late-stage cancer,

728
00:57:05,740 --> 00:57:09,540
do you know what I thought of first?

729
00:57:13,100 --> 00:57:15,860
"I'll get insurance money.

730
00:57:16,810 --> 00:57:22,700
We'll be okay for now, then."

731
00:57:22,700 --> 00:57:25,220
I felt relieved first.

732
00:57:28,650 --> 00:57:31,770
I could've died before him,

733
00:57:31,770 --> 00:57:36,280
but I felt relieved first.

734
00:57:37,770 --> 00:57:44,620
I prayed every day that I lived one day
longer than Myeong Jae,

735
00:57:45,710 --> 00:57:50,200
but I couldn't leave it to Heaven anymore.

736
00:57:50,200 --> 00:57:55,510
Heaven wants to take me away first.

737
00:57:56,750 --> 00:57:59,920
Is that why you had no choice but to do that?

738
00:57:59,920 --> 00:58:04,360
I don't want to say I had no choice.

739
00:58:08,780 --> 00:58:12,040
How could you kill a person and...

740
00:58:12,040 --> 00:58:15,960
say I had no choice but to do that?

741
00:58:15,960 --> 00:58:19,400
But that's the story that brought you here.

742
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:21,940
You need to explain that in court.

743
00:58:23,750 --> 00:58:28,410
I'll die soon, anyway.

744
00:58:30,240 --> 00:58:34,540
I don't even need to ask for a lighter sentence.

745
00:58:36,220 --> 00:58:39,480
I killed my little brother...

746
00:58:45,520 --> 00:58:48,890
with my own hands.

747
00:58:49,750 --> 00:58:51,870
How could I beg for forgiveness?

748
00:58:51,870 --> 00:58:54,400
I'm too ashamed.

749
00:59:00,110 --> 00:59:04,600
Then, only be punished for what you did.

750
00:59:06,160 --> 00:59:09,720
Not all crimes come with the same punishment.

751
00:59:11,170 --> 00:59:14,390
You only get punished for your sin.

752
00:59:14,390 --> 00:59:17,090
And it's my job to explain it.

753
00:59:20,350 --> 00:59:23,010
Please let me do my job.

754
00:59:44,280 --> 00:59:45,500
The call is not going through.

755
00:59:45,500 --> 00:59:49,100
You'll be connected to the
voicemail after the beep.

756
01:00:06,710 --> 01:00:08,120
The call is not going through...

757
01:00:21,610 --> 01:00:23,180
Therefore, the defendant

758
01:00:23,180 --> 01:00:26,560
suffocated Mr. Jeong Myeong Jae,
which led to his death,

759
01:00:26,560 --> 01:00:29,900
resulting in his murder.

760
01:00:30,660 --> 01:00:35,740
Defense counsel, please state your opinion
on the facts of the indictment.

761
01:00:35,740 --> 01:00:38,800
We admit to the charge and
acknowledge the evidence.

762
01:00:38,800 --> 01:00:42,910
Got it. I'll look through the evidence, then.

763
01:01:03,610 --> 01:01:05,730
I finished looking at the evidence.

764
01:01:05,730 --> 01:01:08,890
Prosecutor, please request the sentence.

765
01:01:09,890 --> 01:01:14,390
Please sentence the defendant
to 10 years in prison.

766
01:01:16,190 --> 01:01:19,560
Defense counsel, please state your opinion.

767
01:01:26,890 --> 01:01:29,590
I believe taking someone's life

768
01:01:29,590 --> 01:01:33,610
is unforgivable in every way.

769
01:01:33,610 --> 01:01:36,610
The defendant also agrees,
so she turned herself in

770
01:01:36,610 --> 01:01:40,500
immediately, and she's been admitting the crime.

771
01:01:40,500 --> 01:01:44,180
The defendant was the victim's only guardian.

772
01:01:44,180 --> 01:01:46,170
The victim suffered from severe dementia

773
01:01:46,170 --> 01:01:50,660
and she's been caring for him for over 10 years.

774
01:01:50,660 --> 01:01:54,480
Without being able to get help
from her family and society,

775
01:01:54,480 --> 01:01:58,420
she had to care for him and provide
for herself at the same time.

776
01:02:00,530 --> 01:02:02,590
In that situation,

777
01:02:05,690 --> 01:02:09,340
the defendant was diagnosed
with late-stage cancer recently.

778
01:02:20,290 --> 01:02:24,420
Afraid that she'd depart even
a day before her brother,

779
01:02:24,420 --> 01:02:27,820
she couldn't handle that possibility.

780
01:02:28,620 --> 01:02:30,950
She doesn't seek a generous punishment.

781
01:02:30,950 --> 01:02:36,340
But she wants to be punished
only for what she did.

782
01:02:37,420 --> 01:02:41,370
Her crime was a result
of negligence, repeated isolation,

783
01:02:41,370 --> 01:02:44,650
and prolonged exhaustion.

784
01:02:46,470 --> 01:02:51,180
So, please consider her regretful attitude,

785
01:02:51,180 --> 01:02:54,340
the circumstances that led to the case,

786
01:02:54,340 --> 01:02:58,880
and her physical condition going forward.

787
01:03:10,600 --> 01:03:12,990
I'm sorry, Mom.

788
01:03:19,980 --> 01:03:21,780
Oh, no...

789
01:03:24,170 --> 01:03:26,150
My gosh...

790
01:03:38,130 --> 01:03:40,170
Have you been starving?

791
01:03:40,170 --> 01:03:43,700
I eat too well. So, don't worry about it.

792
01:03:43,700 --> 01:03:45,310
Right, Mom.

793
01:03:45,310 --> 01:03:49,900
You didn't forget the checkup appointment, right?

794
01:03:49,900 --> 01:03:52,410
I said I don't need stuff like that.

795
01:03:52,410 --> 01:03:54,650
I said you need it.

